The paper presents a model-based development methodology and a tool support for verified software systems, which suggests that it could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of the AUTOFOCUS 3 tool chain and its basic principles also suggests that it could belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The emphasis on verification and check mechanisms suggests that it could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of implementation of automatic generators suggests that it could belong to the Emerging Technologies (cs.EM) sub-category.
